    <title>Re: LMS: Due Date based on the completion date of another item inside the same curriculum</title>
    <updated>2024-04-01T21:50:27.569000+02:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>thedeansta1</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/181510</uri>
    </author>
    <content>Hello Karen. I have a similar scenario. We want to assign an item A immediately upon hire with a due date 30 days after start. Then assign a refresher item B one year after completion of item A. If we use your method, upon completion of Item A, Item B will be immediately assigned and show up on their learning page. How do we get Item B to get assigned 1 year after completion of Item A, not show up on their learning page, and still keep a due date of 30 days to complete Item B after assignment?</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/human-capital-management-q-a/re-lms-due-date-based-on-the-completion-date-of-another-item-inside-the/qaq-p/13654955/comment-id/34397#M34397"/>
    <published>2024-04-01T21:50:27.569000+02:00</published>
  </entry>
